  "text": "Lysosome/Phagosome Targeting Vol. 17, April 2006uptake [CITATION_1] . To rule out this possibility, some cells were also labeled with [ 3 H]cholesterol. Whereas cholesteryl ether remains membrane-bound, cholesterol readily exchanges by diffusion [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , and the movement of cholesterol to phagosomes should be independent of membrane fusion [CITATION_4] . In fact, after labeling cells with [ 3 H]cholesterol, cytochalasin D had no effect ( Figure 7A ). Both drugs were also innocuous in cells labeled with [",
